UNOFFICIAL COPY 26 RS BR 2453
1 AN ACT relating to a supplemental payment for retired state employees, making an
2 appropriation therefor, and declaring an emergency.
3 Be it enacted by the General Assembly of the Commonwealth of Kentucky:
4 Section 1. Notwithstanding any provision of KRS 61.691 to the contrary and
5 subject to the limitations established by this section, recipients of a monthly retirement
6 allowance from the Kentucky Employees Retirement System or State Police Retirement
7 System who have been retired for at least 12 months shall receive a one-time
8 supplemental payment added to their July 2026 retirement allowance payment, equal to
9 the monthly retirement allowance the recipient receives from the system in the month of
10 June 2026, not to exceed a maximum payment per recipient of $1,000.
11 Section 2. There is hereby appropriated General Fund moneys in the amount of
12 $43,827,000 in fiscal year 2026-2027 from the budget reserve trust fund account
13 established by KRS 48.705 to the Kentucky Public Pensions Authority to be applied to
14 the following funds to prefund the supplemental payment provided by Section 1 of this
15 Act:
16 (1) $38,488,000 to the Kentucky Employees Retirement Fund of the Kentucky
17 Employees Retirement System established by KRS 61.515 to prefund the supplemental
18 payment from the Kentucky Employees Retirement System to each recipient for service
19 in a nonhazardous position as defined in KRS 61.510(44);
20 (2) $3,748,000 to the Kentucky Employees Retirement Fund of the Kentucky
21 Employees Retirement System established by KRS 61.515 to prefund the supplemental
22 payment from the Kentucky Employees Retirement System to each recipient for service
23 in a hazardous position as provided in KRS 61.592; and
24 (3) $1,591,000 to the State Police Retirement Fund of the State Police Retirement
25 System established by KRS 16.510 to prefund the supplemental payment from the State
26 Police Retirement System to each recipient.
27 Section 3. Whereas retired members and beneficiaries of the Kentucky
